abstract: Labor Dept says weekly applications for unemployment benefits fell 9,000 to seasonally adjusted 282,000.
lead_paragraph: The Labor Department said on Thursday that weekly applications for jobless aid fell 9,000 to a seasonally adjusted 282,000.

headline.main: Fewer U.S. Jobless Claims Suggest a Rebounding Economy
headline.print_headline: Jobless Claims Decline, Pointing to a Rebound
